One of the most essential characteristics of QDs is quantum confinement, which leads to the quantization of energy due to their nanoscale sizes. This phenomenon occurs when the wavefunctions of electrons and holes are shrunk down to dimensions smaller than the excitonic Bohr radius [70]. The confinement energy can be estimated as ΔE=ℏ2π22m∗r2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
